 On Feb  6, Robby Findler wrote:
 > You already can tack all the arrows from a single binder. You want more?
 
 I'm thinking of this demo where the whole layout of a complete toy
 program so it's structure is very obvious -- trying to demonstrate the
 point that we don't care for the names, just for the arrows.  Tacking
 all the arrows from a single id helps a lot (I didn't see that
 option), so I don't know if this is worth bothering about.
